{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e9e8c73b-b882-4e8a-be36-e304293cefbe","content":"Here's a complete migration plan from VSTest to **Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP)** for your setup:\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1 — Update Package References (per test `.csproj`)\n\nReplace the three legacy packages with the unified MSTest SDK or enable MTP mode:\n\n**Option A (recommended) — MSTest SDK style:**\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest/3.8.0\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n</Project>\n```\n\nRemove `MSTest.TestFramework`, `MSTest.TestAdapter`, and `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` — the SDK brings them all in with MTP enabled by default.\n\n**Option B — Property toggle (minimal diff):**\n\nKeep existing `PackageReference` nodes and add to a `Directory.Build.props`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n  <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\nThis makes each test project a self-contained executable using MTP.\n\n---\n\n## Phase 2 — Restore TRX + Code Coverage\n\nMTP doesn't use `runsettings` the same way. Add these extensions:\n\n```xml\n<ItemGroup>\n  <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport\" Version=\"1.6.2\" />\n  <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage\" Version=\"17.13.2\" />\n</ItemGroup>\n```\n\nCLI equivalents at test time:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --results-directory ./TestResults \\\n  -- --report-trx --coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura\n```\n\n---\n\n## Phase 3 — Update Azure DevOps Pipeline\n\nReplace `VSTest@3` with `DotNetCoreCLI@2`:\n\n```yaml\n- task: DotNetCoreCLI@2\n  displayName: 'Run Tests (MTP)'\n  inputs:\n    command: test\n    projects: '**/*Tests.csproj'\n    arguments: >-\n      --results-directory $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n      -- --report-trx --coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura\n\n- task: PublishTestResults@2\n  inputs:\n    testResultsFormat: VSTest\n    testResultsFiles: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.trx'\n\n- task: PublishCodeCoverageResults@2\n  inputs:\n    summaryFileLocation: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.cobertura.xml'\n```\n\n---\n\n## Phase 4 — Validate\n\n1. Run `dotnet test` locally — each test project now launches as its own process.\n2. Confirm TRX files appear in `TestResults/`.\n3. Confirm coverage `.cobertura.xml` files generate.\n4. Run the pipeline; verify **Tests** and **Code Coverage** tabs populate.\n\n---\n\n## Key Differences to Expect\n\n| Aspect | VSTest | MTP |\n|--------|--------|-----|\n| Execution | `vstest.console` hosts tests | Each project is an exe |\n| Parallelism | Controlled by `.runsettings` | `--maximum-failed-tests`, per-project parallel via `dotnet test` |\n| Filters | `--TestCaseFilter` | `--filter` (same syntax) |\n| `.runsettings` | Fully supported | Limited; prefer CLI flags |\n\n---\n\n## Rollback Safety\n\nKeep a feature branch. If issues arise, remove `EnableMSTestRunner`/revert to classic SDK and restore `VSTest@3`. The test code itself requires **zero changes**.\n\nWant me to generate the actual `Directory.Build.props`, updated `.csproj` templates, or pipeline YAML as files?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"30de39c6-bf6c-4e1b-9ef0-737fdfa26e4a","outputTokens":919,"requestId":"BC22:223B6B:1C7F43A:1F9D169:69FA91DE"},"id":"e0084868-f1e9-40cb-ace1-8ad0c8be32e1","timestamp":"2026-05-06T00:57:21.218Z","parentId":"23608477-7748-448b-b427-fcb847f0e9ac"}
